            "text": "Diagnostic testing for the novel coronavirus is an important tool",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "to fight the coronavirus disease ( Covid-19 ) pandemic . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "However , testing capacities are limited . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "A modified testing protocol ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "whereby a number of probes are ' pooled ' ( i.e. grouped ) ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "is known to increase the capacity for testing . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "Here , we model pooled testing with a double - average model ,",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "which we think to be close to reality for Covid-19 testing . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "The optimal pool size and the effect of test errors are considered . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "The results show",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that the best pool size is three to five , under reasonable assumptions . <S>",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "Pool testing even reduces the number of false positives in the absence of dilution effects . <S> <P>",
